  "text": "Nuclear proteins were extracted, and a 5-g aliquot was incubated with either a ␥-32 P-labeled double-stranded DNA probe (ϳ2.5 ng) containing a B site from the class I major histocompatibility complex promoter or a constitutive nuclear protein (Oct-1, sc-232, Santa Cruz Biotechnology; Santa Cruz, CA) to control for protein loading and separated by EMSA as described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ",
